  "prompt": "What is NOT enlightenment?",
  "response": "Here are some things that are NOT enlightenment:\n\n1. Intellectual knowledge\n- Simply understanding spiritual concepts\n- Reading about spirituality\n- Accumulating philosophical information\n\n2. Temporary experiences\n- Fleeting mystical experiences\n- Momentary states of bliss\n- Short-lived altered consciousness\n\n3. Ego-driven spiritual pursuits\n- Seeking spiritual status\n- Using spirituality to feel superior\n- Spiritual competition or comparison\n\n4. Emotional states\n- Feeling peaceful\n- Experiencing temporary happiness\n- Emotional highs\n\n5. Psychological techniques\n- Meditation without deeper understanding\n- Practicing mindfulness mechanically\n- Self-improvement without inner transformation\n\n6. External practices\n- Performing rituals\n- Wearing spiritual clothing\n- Following specific dietary restrictions\n\n7. Magical thinking\n- Believing in supernatural powers\n- Expecting instant solutions\n- Seeking miraculous interventions\n\n8. Escape from reality\n- Avoiding life's challenges\n- Withdrawing from responsibilities\n- Spiritual bypassing\n\nTrue enlightenment involves:\n- Profound inner transformation\n- Transcendence of ego\n- Deep understanding of reality\n- Compassionate awareness\n- Fundamental shift in consciousness\n\nEnlightenment is a comprehensive, lived experience of profound understanding and interconnectedness.",
